WEBVTT

1
00:00:02.566 --> 00:00:05.694
[Speaking Arabic]

2
00:00:43.974 --> 00:00:45.066
Taxi!

3
00:00:45.208 --> 00:00:46.197
Taxi!

4
00:01:29.986 --> 00:01:32.682
Roger Burke. you ugly fuck!
What are you doing in London?

5
00:01:32.756 --> 00:01:34.690
Get your hands off me.

6
00:01:34.858 --> 00:01:37.019
Put them up.
Put them up.
you fat. wet puss!

7
00:01:37.093 --> 00:01:38.856
Let's show these limey fucks
what we're made of.

8
00:01:38.929 --> 00:01:41.625
Hey. wait a minute!
Who the fuck...
Who do you think this is then?

9
00:01:41.698 --> 00:01:42.995
Roger Burke.
Who do you think this is?

10
00:01:43.066 --> 00:01:45.899
No. you idiot. That is not...
Lay off him. asshole.

11
00:01:46.002 --> 00:01:48.664
That's not him. Come on.
It's Roger Burke.

12
00:01:49.372 --> 00:01:50.532
I'm sorry about my friend.
you know?

13
00:01:50.607 --> 00:01:53.940
He's a fucked-up.
belligerent guy with
a serious drinking problem.

14
00:01:54.010 --> 00:01:57.468
Hey. come here.
Lose it.

15
00:01:57.547 --> 00:01:59.845
Come on. Calm down!
Hey. calm down.

16
00:01:59.916 --> 00:02:02.441
Hey. come here!
Calm down!

17
00:02:05.088 --> 00:02:08.615
Back off. Get back!

18
00:02:08.692 --> 00:02:10.990
Back off! Back off!
Fuck off!

19
00:02:11.061 --> 00:02:12.528
It's me. All right!

20
00:02:12.596 --> 00:02:14.826
All right. Come on.
Fuck off!

21
00:02:15.265 --> 00:02:17.631
It's me. Roger. Orrin!
Come on.

22
00:02:17.701 --> 00:02:22.035
It's me. Remember me? Sorry.
It's all right.

23
00:02:23.139 --> 00:02:25.369
You should have ducked.
Roger!

24
00:02:32.249 --> 00:02:33.841
Fucking Americans!

25
00:02:33.917 --> 00:02:35.680
What the fuck is that?
Was it Salameh?

26
00:02:35.752 --> 00:02:37.913
Yes. of course
it was fucking Salameh!

27
00:02:56.439 --> 00:02:58.100
[Soft piano music playing]

28
00:02:59.743 --> 00:03:02.268
I take it she'd
eat you up a bit. huh?

29
00:03:03.647 --> 00:03:05.239
You old dog.

30
00:03:05.515 --> 00:03:07.278
He's got some ideas.

31
00:03:08.652 --> 00:03:11.143
Oh. the American bloke?
Arert we all?

32
00:03:11.588 --> 00:03:14.318
So you've heard these rumors?
These are wild stories.

33
00:03:14.391 --> 00:03:16.359
Wild stories.
Yeah?

34
00:03:16.426 --> 00:03:17.415
Yeah.

35
00:03:42.452 --> 00:03:43.612
Can I?

36
00:03:51.761 --> 00:03:56.061
I have to go to bed soon.
I work in the morning.

37
00:03:57.067 --> 00:03:59.194
What kind of work do you do?

38
00:04:01.871 --> 00:04:04.305
The kind that drives you
to drink.

39
00:04:05.075 --> 00:04:06.804
We must have the same job.
then.

40
00:04:08.778 --> 00:04:10.507
I love your accent.

41
00:04:11.514 --> 00:04:13.072
I love your perfume.

42
00:04:23.593 --> 00:04:25.788
Cuts right through
the smoke.

43
00:04:27.764 --> 00:04:28.992
Does it?

44
00:04:30.166 --> 00:04:31.929
It's very nice.

45
00:04:36.806 --> 00:04:39.969
Look. I don't want
to be forward...

46
00:04:40.677 --> 00:04:42.269
but it's late...

47
00:04:42.746 --> 00:04:46.045
and I do have to get up early.

48
00:04:46.716 --> 00:04:47.876
So...

49
00:04:49.552 --> 00:04:51.952
So?
So...

50
00:04:53.590 --> 00:04:55.785
So. you're very nice. and...

51
00:04:59.295 --> 00:05:01.820
Are you really going
to make me ask?

52
00:05:08.705 --> 00:05:09.967
I just can't.

53
00:05:11.341 --> 00:05:12.330
Pity.

54
00:05:13.176 --> 00:05:15.838
You're very attractive.
I know.

55
00:05:18.982 --> 00:05:20.574
If you come to your senses...

56
00:05:20.650 --> 00:05:23.244
once you get up
to your lonely room...

57
00:05:23.486 --> 00:05:25.477
well. maybe I'll be here.

58
00:05:26.423 --> 00:05:30.792
Or maybe I'll be in my room.
alone in bed.

59
00:05:37.701 --> 00:05:39.066
Good night.

60
00:05:58.655 --> 00:06:01.920
The drunk Americans.
You think they were CIA?

61
00:06:02.692 --> 00:06:06.093
They could've been.
For all we know. Louis is CIA.

62
00:06:06.162 --> 00:06:08.824
They work both sides.
Everyone does.

63
00:06:08.898 --> 00:06:11.867
Or Louis is Mossad.
Now. maybe he isn't...

64
00:06:11.935 --> 00:06:13.596
but they're using him
to feed us information.

65
00:06:13.670 --> 00:06:15.262
There's no direct link.

66
00:06:15.338 --> 00:06:18.205
Or Mossad's giving it to CIA.
which is giving it to Louis...

67
00:06:18.274 --> 00:06:20.105
and Ephraim's demanding
we give him Louis...

68
00:06:20.176 --> 00:06:22.667
because he knows
we expect him to do...

69
00:06:22.746 --> 00:06:25.647
Stop chasing the mice
inside your skull.

70
00:06:30.754 --> 00:06:33.689
You know.
I never thought you'd last.

71
00:06:34.924 --> 00:06:36.892
I thought the same about you.

72
00:06:36.960 --> 00:06:39.690
From the beginning
you seemed so reluctant.

73
00:06:39.763 --> 00:06:41.628
I was born reluctant.
Ask my mother.

74
00:06:41.698 --> 00:06:43.359
If I can't kvetch.
I can't do my job.

75
00:06:43.433 --> 00:06:45.401
You ever feel reluctant?

76
00:06:45.735 --> 00:06:47.999
I'm not comfortable
with confusion.

77
00:06:49.305 --> 00:06:51.705
I knew guys like you
in the army.

78
00:06:52.075 --> 00:06:54.635
You'll do any terrifying thing
you're asked to do...

79
00:06:54.711 --> 00:06:56.941
but you have to do it running.

80
00:06:58.047 --> 00:07:02.279
You think you can outrun
your fears. your doubts.

81
00:07:04.154 --> 00:07:08.989
The only thing that really
scares you guys is stillness.

82
00:07:10.960 --> 00:07:13.861
But everyone's overtaken.
eventually.

83
00:07:15.632 --> 00:07:18.226
Now. the mice need a brandy.
Will you join me?

84
00:07:18.301 --> 00:07:20.895
No. I'm going to go upstairs.
straight to bed.

85
00:07:20.970 --> 00:07:22.198
You okay drinking
by yourself?

86
00:07:22.272 --> 00:07:24.968
It's just a shot
to numb the brain.
Good night.

87
00:07:28.711 --> 00:07:29.700
Oh.

88
00:07:30.213 --> 00:07:33.114
Beware of the local
honey trap.
Indeed?

89
00:07:34.050 --> 00:07:36.814
You can't miss her.
You don't want to.

90
00:07:48.998 --> 00:07:50.329
[Phone ringing]

91
00:07:57.507 --> 00:07:58.667
Hello.

92
00:07:58.775 --> 00:08:00.970
This is a trunk call
from Mr. Storsch.

93
00:08:01.044 --> 00:08:02.306
Do you accept the charges?

94
00:08:02.378 --> 00:08:05.541
Shit. Avner.
you woke up the baby.
but that's okay... I mean...

95
00:08:05.615 --> 00:08:07.014
How are you?

96
00:08:08.151 --> 00:08:09.277
I miss you.

97
00:08:10.119 --> 00:08:13.247
You're in England
or Australia...

98
00:08:13.323 --> 00:08:15.723
or the North Pole...
Yeah. that's right.

99
00:08:17.794 --> 00:08:19.955
So listen. I was thinking...

100
00:08:20.029 --> 00:08:22.862
when I'm finished doing
what I'm doing here...

101
00:08:22.932 --> 00:08:24.593
I want to come to Brooklyn
to see you.

102
00:08:24.667 --> 00:08:27.465
Brooklyn is depressing.
It's got more churches
than Jerusalem.

103
00:08:27.537 --> 00:08:28.697
Listen to her talk.

104
00:08:28.771 --> 00:08:30.068
[Baby gurgling]

105
00:08:31.374 --> 00:08:34.434
Can you hear me?
Can she hear me?
Yeah. yeah.

106
00:08:35.411 --> 00:08:38.608
Hey. Talk to me.

107
00:08:41.251 --> 00:08:43.719
Daphna. make her talk.

108
00:08:46.089 --> 00:08:47.147
[Baby gurgling]

109
00:08:54.197 --> 00:08:55.186
Dada.

110
00:09:00.136 --> 00:09:03.230
[Whispering] Hey.
Hey. sweetheart.
It's your papa.

111
00:09:05.375 --> 00:09:07.400
This is my voice. darling.

112
00:09:09.712 --> 00:09:12.704
This is what I sound like.
Don't forget. okay?

113
00:09:14.951 --> 00:09:17.852
Listen. I have to get
her to bed. She's tired.

114
00:09:17.921 --> 00:09:19.821
She'll dream about you.

115
00:09:52.355 --> 00:09:56.189
REPORTER: We're standing at
a distance. as instructed
by the terrorists.

116
00:09:57.393 --> 00:09:59.918
Are we going?
Is it to the airport?

117
00:09:59.996 --> 00:10:01.258
Can we talk to someone.
just to say...

118
00:10:01.331 --> 00:10:03.299
Shut up. okay?
Just get on the bus. okay?

119
00:10:03.366 --> 00:10:06.927
Just to tell our families.
Just to say we are all right!

120
00:10:07.070 --> 00:10:09.834
Everybody. just relax. okay?
Relax! Calm down.

121
00:10:09.906 --> 00:10:14.002
We will ride this bus
and fly away. After.
you go back to your home...

122
00:10:14.077 --> 00:10:16.068
or to your Olympic Games.

123
00:10:26.756 --> 00:10:28.121
[Reporters chattering]

124
00:10:32.128 --> 00:10:34.460
[Police dogs barking]

125
00:11:02.091 --> 00:11:03.080
[Groaning]

126
00:11:06.095 --> 00:11:07.494
[Exclaiming]

127
00:11:07.930 --> 00:11:09.659
[Shouting]

128
00:11:19.475 --> 00:11:21.943
[Speaking Hebrew]

129
00:11:23.379 --> 00:11:25.472
[Speaking Arabic]

130
00:11:30.887 --> 00:11:31.876
[Gasping]

131
00:11:59.315 --> 00:12:00.304
[Sniffing]

132
00:12:14.130 --> 00:12:16.963
Carl. You asshole.

133
00:12:17.767 --> 00:12:19.394
I saw her first.

134
00:12:37.787 --> 00:12:38.947
Carl?

135
00:13:40.783 --> 00:13:42.683
[Screaming]

136
00:14:16.419 --> 00:14:19.786
She's Dutch. not political.
entirely business-minded.

137
00:14:20.323 --> 00:14:22.848
She lives in Hoorn.
She's there now.

138
00:14:23.459 --> 00:14:25.484
This is dependable
information.

139
00:14:25.561 --> 00:14:27.586
For which you pay nothing.

140
00:14:27.863 --> 00:14:30.525
We're giving you this.
You understand why?

141
00:14:30.600 --> 00:14:32.864
Because you want me to believe
that you had nothing to do...

142
00:14:32.935 --> 00:14:34.800
with the murder of my partner.

143
00:14:34.870 --> 00:14:38.397
We inabit a world
of intersecting secrecies.

144
00:14:38.774 --> 00:14:42.301
We live and die at the places
where those secrecies meet.

145
00:14:42.378 --> 00:14:44.278
That's what we accept.

146
00:14:45.147 --> 00:14:48.082
We buy information for you
from your enemies.

147
00:14:49.552 --> 00:14:50.712
This alerts them.

148
00:14:50.786 --> 00:14:53.084
You're not the only people
looking for names.

149
00:14:54.090 --> 00:14:56.081
You're telling me
I'm being hunted now?

150
00:14:56.158 --> 00:14:59.059
He's telling you
it's time for you to quit.

151
00:14:59.128 --> 00:15:02.928
The race is not
to the swift. nor
the battle to the strong...

152
00:15:03.032 --> 00:15:05.728
but time and chance
happens to them all.

153
00:15:18.414 --> 00:15:20.177
Evil falls suddenly.

154
00:15:22.485 --> 00:15:24.510
Who can say when it falls?

155
00:15:31.761 --> 00:15:33.956
[Announcements over PA
in French]

156
00:15:47.910 --> 00:15:50.242
So you're really gonna
kill her?

157
00:15:51.580 --> 00:15:55.641
All this blood comes back
to us.
Eventually it will work.

158
00:15:56.085 --> 00:15:58.781
Even if it takes years.
we'll beat them.

159
00:15:59.822 --> 00:16:01.483
We're Jews. Avner.

160
00:16:02.058 --> 00:16:04.151
Jews don't do wrong
because our enemies do wrong.

161
00:16:04.226 --> 00:16:06.694
We can't afford to be
that decent anymore.

162
00:16:06.796 --> 00:16:08.957
I don't know that
we ever were that decent.

163
00:16:09.365 --> 00:16:13.267
Suffering thousands of years
of hatred doesn't make you
decent.

164
00:16:13.536 --> 00:16:17.233
But we're
supposed to be righteous.
That's a beautiful thing.

165
00:16:17.306 --> 00:16:18.671
That's Jewish.

166
00:16:18.741 --> 00:16:20.902
That's what I knew.
that's what I was taught.

167
00:16:22.111 --> 00:16:24.875
And now I'm losing it.
and I lose that. that's...

168
00:16:24.980 --> 00:16:27.107
That's...
That's everything.

169
00:16:27.783 --> 00:16:29.307
That's my soul.

170
00:16:32.288 --> 00:16:35.451
You need to go rest somewhere.
You don't have to do this one.

171
00:16:37.693 --> 00:16:39.558
When I need you again.
I'll find you.

172
00:16:53.109 --> 00:16:54.508
[Train whistle blaring]

173
00:17:22.004 --> 00:17:24.199
[Radio playing]

174
00:17:33.015 --> 00:17:35.176
Excuse me. Who are you?

175
00:17:43.492 --> 00:17:44.982
Do you know why we're here?

176
00:17:45.694 --> 00:17:47.184
I want to get dressed. okay?

177
00:17:53.669 --> 00:17:56.866
Maybe you want to hire me.
You know how good I am.

178
00:18:02.178 --> 00:18:03.304
No. Don't.

179
00:18:04.146 --> 00:18:06.671
It's such a fucking waste
of talent.

180
00:18:18.294 --> 00:18:20.125
Where're you going?
Stay here.

181
00:18:20.196 --> 00:18:21.663
Shell. Shell.

182
00:18:22.565 --> 00:18:23.657
Yeah.

183
00:18:41.283 --> 00:18:42.272
[Gasping]

184
00:18:59.602 --> 00:19:00.864
Leave it.

185
00:19:19.121 --> 00:19:22.284
HANS: In seven months
we've killed six
of the 11 names.

186
00:19:23.092 --> 00:19:25.322
We've killed one replacement.

187
00:19:25.661 --> 00:19:27.754
One of our targets
is in prison and four...

188
00:19:27.830 --> 00:19:30.663
including Ali Hassan Salameh.
are at large.

189
00:19:31.567 --> 00:19:33.592
One of our own has fallen.

190
00:19:34.403 --> 00:19:37.429
Since we began. the other side
has sent letter bombs
to 11 embassies...

191
00:19:37.506 --> 00:19:39.474
hijacked three planes...

192
00:19:39.975 --> 00:19:43.604
killed 130 passengers
in Athens and wounded
scores more...

193
00:19:44.246 --> 00:19:46.874
and killed our military
attache in Washington.

194
00:19:46.982 --> 00:19:50.418
Some of it was
done by a Venezuelan
called Carlos the Jackal...

195
00:19:50.486 --> 00:19:52.386
who replaced Zaid Muchassi...

196
00:19:52.488 --> 00:19:54.683
who replaced Hussein al-Chir.

197
00:19:55.824 --> 00:19:59.385
Black September's original
leadership has been decimated.

198
00:20:01.463 --> 00:20:03.761
But new leaders
are emerging...

199
00:20:04.033 --> 00:20:06.627
for whom Black September
wasrt violent enough.

200
00:20:09.638 --> 00:20:12.232
And to dispatch
our six dispatched targets...

201
00:20:12.308 --> 00:20:15.607
we must have spent something
close to $2 million. right?

202
00:20:15.678 --> 00:20:19.011
You've been cooking.
Are you expecting company?

203
00:20:19.915 --> 00:20:22.247
Mrs. Meir
says to the Knesset...

204
00:20:24.053 --> 00:20:26.681
the world must see
that killing Jews...

205
00:20:26.889 --> 00:20:29.824
will be from now on
an expensive proposition.

206
00:20:32.061 --> 00:20:34.359
But killing Palestinians
isn't exactly cheap.

207
00:20:38.000 --> 00:20:41.595
If all 11 were dead.
you'd stop?
Yes.

208
00:20:42.871 --> 00:20:46.967
You're lying.
What about their replacements?

209
00:20:47.710 --> 00:20:50.543
With each time we kill.
we create six more.

210
00:20:51.480 --> 00:20:53.277
Maybe they'll have to keep
killing them. then.

211
00:20:53.349 --> 00:20:54.577
Forever.

212
00:20:55.784 --> 00:20:57.877
Five targets are still alive.

213
00:20:57.953 --> 00:20:59.944
That's five men
that need to be killed.

214
00:21:00.022 --> 00:21:02.582
Eventually you forget that
in the beginning you hated
doing it.

215
00:21:02.658 --> 00:21:04.250
For me personally.
I feel less every day.

216
00:21:04.326 --> 00:21:06.351
One day I'm going to wake up.
I'm going to kill...

217
00:21:06.428 --> 00:21:09.420
I'm going to go back to bed.
I'm not going to feel anything
at all.

218
00:21:11.500 --> 00:21:15.664
Hey. Hans? You know there's
a rule in the book against
blind drunks.

219
00:21:15.938 --> 00:21:17.838
Why don't you stop drinking
and eat something?

220
00:21:17.906 --> 00:21:21.205
I mean. there's enough food
here to feed Bangladesh.

221
00:21:24.213 --> 00:21:27.876
I keep seeing that
Dutch woman. you know.
sprawled out like that.

222
00:21:31.353 --> 00:21:34.254
It's not that I wish
we hadrt killed her.

223
00:21:34.556 --> 00:21:37.354
I wish I had let you
close up her housecoat.

224
00:21:37.926 --> 00:21:41.487
Yeah.
but you werert yourself.

225
00:21:56.412 --> 00:21:57.572
[Whispering] Avner.

226
00:22:00.482 --> 00:22:01.471
Avner.

227
00:22:04.053 --> 00:22:05.042
Avner.

228
00:22:05.621 --> 00:22:08.613
I went to Hans' flat
above the antique shop...

229
00:22:09.191 --> 00:22:12.126
just to check up on him
because he was so...

230
00:22:13.128 --> 00:22:15.995
Anyway. he's gone somewhere.
and I waited all night...

231
00:22:16.065 --> 00:22:17.692
and he's not come back.

232
00:22:38.821 --> 00:22:39.981
Knife.

233
00:22:45.094 --> 00:22:47.119
They didn't take anything.

234
00:27:01.149 --> 00:27:02.411
[Phone ringing]

235
00:27:09.257 --> 00:27:10.315
What?

236
00:27:41.256 --> 00:27:43.053
It will be beautiful.

237
00:27:44.526 --> 00:27:47.984
LOUIS: Ali Hassan Salameh
is in Tarifa on the Spanish
coast.

238
00:27:49.064 --> 00:27:52.693
He's at a compound
guarded by all the
predictable trouble.

239
00:27:53.068 --> 00:27:55.798
Bomb makers often die
accidental deaths.

240
00:27:58.206 --> 00:28:00.504
In Athens
you shot a KGB agent.

241
00:28:02.611 --> 00:28:05.910
Many people must want
to kill you. Monsieur Storsch.

242
00:28:06.314 --> 00:28:09.613
But why would I do that?
You pay better than anyone.

243
00:28:15.157 --> 00:28:17.648
It's dangerous
going after Salameh.

244
00:28:18.960 --> 00:28:20.825
But he planned
the Munich massacre.

245
00:28:24.966 --> 00:28:28.697
Eliminate him.
and they'll let you go home.
Don't you think?

246
00:28:32.207 --> 00:28:33.834
Yes. Louis. I do.

247
00:28:37.879 --> 00:28:40.712
You could have a kitchen
like that someday.

248
00:28:43.819 --> 00:28:47.619
It costs dearly.
but home always does.

249
00:29:27.162 --> 00:29:28.993
[Festive voices]

250
00:29:44.312 --> 00:29:46.803
Shit!
It's like a funouse in there.

251
00:29:47.616 --> 00:29:49.481
Can you tell how many?

252
00:30:09.271 --> 00:30:10.670
That's him.

253
00:30:15.177 --> 00:30:17.372
Are you sure it's him. Avner?

254
00:30:19.047 --> 00:30:20.810
You have to be sure.

255
00:30:32.060 --> 00:30:33.049
[Yelling in Arabic]

256
00:31:23.011 --> 00:31:24.706
I'm Avner Kaufman.
We know.

257
00:31:24.779 --> 00:31:27.179
You want to ride with us?
Hop in.

258
00:31:27.582 --> 00:31:28.879
Please.

259
00:31:34.723 --> 00:31:37.749
I'm Amos.
This is Avi. Shin Bet.

260
00:31:38.660 --> 00:31:40.287
We're not supposed to know
who you are...

261
00:31:41.463 --> 00:31:42.452
because we're not officers.

262
00:31:42.764 --> 00:31:45.494
We're just shit
and no one tells us shit.

263
00:31:47.302 --> 00:31:49.930
We've heard about
what you've done.

264
00:31:51.940 --> 00:31:54.170
We want to say
it's an honor
to meet you.

265
00:31:59.414 --> 00:32:01.473
It's an honor for me.
too.

266
00:32:10.925 --> 00:32:13.257
I have no problems
with anything you guys did...

267
00:32:13.328 --> 00:32:16.161
except the woman
on the houseboat
in Hoorn.

268
00:32:16.798 --> 00:32:18.527
Steve's told us about her.

269
00:32:18.600 --> 00:32:19.794
We took a leave
of absence...

270
00:32:19.868 --> 00:32:21.199
and killed her
off the company clock.

271
00:32:21.269 --> 00:32:22.327
Don't be an idiot.

272
00:32:22.404 --> 00:32:25.464
Otherwise. as I said.
we have no problems
with the job you did.

273
00:32:26.408 --> 00:32:28.535
Except three
of my men died.

274
00:32:28.610 --> 00:32:29.702
According
to your colleague...

275
00:32:29.778 --> 00:32:31.905
I should say. emphatically.
according to your colleague...

276
00:32:31.980 --> 00:32:33.538
not in any way your fault.

277
00:32:33.615 --> 00:32:34.775
He sings your praises.

278
00:32:34.849 --> 00:32:37.409
Best guy he ever worked for.
and so on.

279
00:32:41.323 --> 00:32:44.486
He says this French group...
Louis was his name?

280
00:32:44.759 --> 00:32:47.785
They sold
the terrorists information
regarding your whereabouts.

281
00:32:47.862 --> 00:32:49.557
They helped kill your men.

282
00:32:50.865 --> 00:32:53.129
I know Steve believes that.
but it's not true.

283
00:32:53.201 --> 00:32:54.498
Tell us who they are.

284
00:32:57.105 --> 00:32:59.096
They won't work with you.

285
00:33:00.542 --> 00:33:03.636
It's about loyalty.
You're an Israeli officer.

286
00:33:03.812 --> 00:33:06.372
That's your only loyalty!
That's it!

287
00:33:09.417 --> 00:33:10.509
Okay.

288
00:33:11.986 --> 00:33:14.921
This is General Hofi
of the Northern Command.

289
00:33:15.090 --> 00:33:16.580
You look good.

290
00:33:17.292 --> 00:33:20.819
Listen. the Prime Minister
is proud of you and your men.

291
00:33:20.995 --> 00:33:23.020
She wishes she could tell you
herself. but she can't.

292
00:33:23.098 --> 00:33:25.032
She never heard of you.
right?

293
00:33:25.834 --> 00:33:29.292
Good. She says you've done
a great thing for your people.

294
00:33:29.371 --> 00:33:30.736
For Israel.

295
00:33:35.176 --> 00:33:38.009
That's it.
There is no medal or anything.

296
00:33:49.657 --> 00:33:52.717
June 16. 1973.
Avner Kaufman interview.

297
00:33:55.196 --> 00:33:56.458
Go ahead.

298
00:34:00.835 --> 00:34:02.826
Tell me what you learned.

299
00:34:05.807 --> 00:34:07.707
What I learned?
Yes.

300
00:34:07.942 --> 00:34:09.671
What did you learn?

301
00:34:12.313 --> 00:34:13.746
For God's sake!

302
00:34:13.915 --> 00:34:16.281
Tell me the names and numbers
of your sources.

303
00:34:20.655 --> 00:34:22.145
Avner. tell me.

304
00:34:22.223 --> 00:34:25.215
Tell me the names and numbers
of your sources.

305
00:34:26.628 --> 00:34:27.822
Please.

306
00:34:29.097 --> 00:34:31.998
I can have you
court-martialed. and I might.

307
00:34:32.734 --> 00:34:35.862
You can't.
I don't work for you.

308
00:34:37.806 --> 00:34:39.296
I don't exist.

309
00:34:41.643 --> 00:34:44.544
You look terrible.
I'm not good right now.

310
00:34:47.115 --> 00:34:50.949
You don't
need to tell me anything.
It's taken a lot from you.

311
00:34:51.653 --> 00:34:55.680
I'm alive. right?
And the rest sorts
itself out.

312
00:34:57.192 --> 00:35:00.628
I'm not a fool. Avner.
I never said
you were a fool.

313
00:35:10.705 --> 00:35:14.505
Everyone in Europe died.
Most of my family.

314
00:35:15.477 --> 00:35:16.967
A huge family.

315
00:35:17.045 --> 00:35:18.376
[Making blowing sound]

316
00:35:20.615 --> 00:35:22.913
I never talked
to you about it.

317
00:35:23.151 --> 00:35:26.086
I knew.
You knew?
So what was there to say?

318
00:35:27.555 --> 00:35:29.955
I didn't die.
because I came here.

319
00:35:30.291 --> 00:35:33.727
When I arrived.
I walked up to the top
of a hill in Jerusalem...

320
00:35:33.795 --> 00:35:36.730
and prayed for a child.

321
00:35:36.998 --> 00:35:39.990
I never prayed before.
but I was praying then.

322
00:35:40.068 --> 00:35:43.333
And I could feel every
one of them praying with me.

323
00:35:46.875 --> 00:35:48.968
You are what we prayed for.

324
00:35:50.111 --> 00:35:52.306
What you did.
you did for us.

325
00:35:52.747 --> 00:35:55.580
You did for your daughter.
but also for us.

326
00:35:55.950 --> 00:35:59.181
Every one of the ones
who died. died wanting this.

327
00:36:00.822 --> 00:36:04.451
We had to take it.
because no one
will ever give it to us.

328
00:36:04.592 --> 00:36:07.823
A place to be
a Jew among Jews.
subject to no one.

329
00:36:09.964 --> 00:36:12.398
I thank God for hearing
my prayer.

330
00:36:14.569 --> 00:36:16.594
Do you want to know. Mama?

331
00:36:18.139 --> 00:36:20.699
Do you want me to tell you
what I did?

332
00:36:22.710 --> 00:36:23.734
No.

333
00:36:25.213 --> 00:36:28.649
Whatever it took.
whatever it takes.

334
00:36:30.552 --> 00:36:35.512
A place on Earth.
We have a place on Earth.

335
00:36:36.958 --> 00:36:38.220
At last.

336
00:36:48.102 --> 00:36:50.195
What's this?
Baklava.

337
00:36:51.072 --> 00:36:54.269
From Rehovot?
The only edible baklava
is from the Arabs in Jaffa.

338
00:36:54.342 --> 00:36:56.537
Eat it on the plane.
You're too thin.

339
00:36:56.644 --> 00:36:58.669
I hope it gives you
a bellyache.

340
00:37:00.114 --> 00:37:01.479
Listen. forget it.

341
00:37:01.549 --> 00:37:04.245
You go see
your wife. your child.
rest for a few more months.

342
00:37:04.319 --> 00:37:06.048
Then we're gonna put you
back in the field.

343
00:37:06.120 --> 00:37:07.883
Not Europe.
Probably Latin America.

344
00:37:07.956 --> 00:37:11.153
You think it over.
Rest. Avner.
Then you come back.

345
00:37:13.428 --> 00:37:14.452
No.

346
00:37:21.803 --> 00:37:23.430
[Church bells tolling]

347
00:37:41.422 --> 00:37:42.514
That's all right.

348
00:37:42.590 --> 00:37:46.048
Oh. no. no. no.
It's okay. It's okay.

349
00:37:46.127 --> 00:37:49.290
Look at that beautiful hair.

350
00:38:36.277 --> 00:38:37.642
Nightmares?

351
00:38:38.780 --> 00:38:39.838
Yes.

352
00:38:43.284 --> 00:38:44.876
Come back to bed.

353
00:38:47.455 --> 00:38:49.821
I have no idea
where I should be.

354
00:38:56.197 --> 00:39:00.657
The place is nice.
You've made it really nice.

355
00:39:01.969 --> 00:39:03.834
The kitchers too big.

356
00:40:21.816 --> 00:40:24.444
Sylvie. I need to speak
to your father.

357
00:40:26.554 --> 00:40:28.078
Is Louis there?

358
00:40:29.757 --> 00:40:32.487
I need to speak
to your father.
Have him call me.

359
00:40:32.560 --> 00:40:36.360
212-664-7665.

360
00:40:37.064 --> 00:40:39.532
I'll wait. He must call me.
I'll wait.

361
00:40:40.535 --> 00:40:41.968
[Phone ringing]

362
00:40:43.771 --> 00:40:45.295
Am I being hunted?

363
00:40:45.973 --> 00:40:47.600
Is my family being hunted?

364
00:40:47.675 --> 00:40:52.635
How is your father?
He's well?
Your family is well?

365
00:40:52.780 --> 00:40:56.341
I don't know.
How is my family?
Are they well?

366
00:40:56.417 --> 00:40:57.782
Are they going to be okay?

367
00:40:57.852 --> 00:41:00.548
I'm sending you a parcel
of sausage and cheese.

368
00:41:00.688 --> 00:41:03.782
Real cheese.
The kind you can't
find in America.

369
00:41:03.925 --> 00:41:07.417
It isn't pasteurized.
so it won't taste like shit.

370
00:41:08.763 --> 00:41:11.755
It's a real pleasure
to hear your voice again.

371
00:41:12.900 --> 00:41:15.164
I think about you
with concern.

372
00:41:15.636 --> 00:41:17.228
Do you believe me?

373
00:41:19.273 --> 00:41:20.262
Avner?

374
00:41:21.142 --> 00:41:23.007
You believe me. Avner?

375
00:41:25.213 --> 00:41:26.874
You know my name?

376
00:41:26.948 --> 00:41:28.472
Of course I do.

377
00:41:30.151 --> 00:41:32.085
Now. listen to me.
It's important.

378
00:41:33.487 --> 00:41:36.354
No harm will come to you
from me.

379
00:41:39.493 --> 00:41:40.482
[Phone clicking]

380
00:41:41.062 --> 00:41:42.256
[Dial tone]

381
00:42:01.349 --> 00:42:04.876
You can't go in there. sir.
It's a restricted area. Sir?

382
00:42:05.586 --> 00:42:07.713
I tried to stop him.
I don't know who this guy is.

383
00:42:07.788 --> 00:42:10.348
Security!

384
00:42:11.659 --> 00:42:13.320
If you're Mossad.
you know who I am.

385
00:42:13.394 --> 00:42:16.261
If you don't.
tell Ephraim Avner
came to see him.

386
00:42:16.330 --> 00:42:17.763
Being in this room
is by appointment only.

387
00:42:17.865 --> 00:42:19.355
Shut up and listen to me.

388
00:42:19.433 --> 00:42:21.958
I won't hesitate to kill
other people's children...

389
00:42:22.036 --> 00:42:24.061
if you hurt my child.
Understand?
Do I know you. sir?

390
00:42:24.138 --> 00:42:27.232
Or wives if you hurt my wife.
or fathers if you hurt
my father.

391
00:42:27.308 --> 00:42:29.538
I don't care.
I'll go to the newspapers.

392
00:42:29.610 --> 00:42:32.511
I'll give every name
of everybody who was
in the meetings.

393
00:42:32.580 --> 00:42:36.277
I'll tell them everything
if you don't leave
my family alone! Okay?

394
00:46:26.914 --> 00:46:28.176
[Screaming]

395
00:47:05.319 --> 00:47:06.684
I love you.

396
00:47:31.545 --> 00:47:32.705
Avner.

397
00:47:38.285 --> 00:47:39.775
Phone for you.

398
00:47:40.321 --> 00:47:41.788
He's Israeli.

399
00:47:46.727 --> 00:47:49.059
You think we'd hurt
your family?

400
00:47:49.496 --> 00:47:52.090
I think anyone is capable
of anything.

401
00:47:52.499 --> 00:47:54.831
I think you're losing
your mind.

402
00:47:59.807 --> 00:48:01.570
Did I commit murder?

403
00:48:04.778 --> 00:48:06.871
I want you to give me proof
that everyone we killed...

404
00:48:06.947 --> 00:48:08.005
had a hand in Munich.

405
00:48:08.082 --> 00:48:10.414
I don't discuss such things
with people who don't exist.

406
00:48:10.484 --> 00:48:13.009
You want to discuss.
come back to existence.

407
00:48:13.087 --> 00:48:15.112
You want your daughter
to grow up in exile?

408
00:48:15.189 --> 00:48:16.781
I want evidence.

409
00:48:20.494 --> 00:48:23.861
Professor Hamshari
with the beautiful wife
and child?

410
00:48:24.198 --> 00:48:27.497
He was implicated
in a failed assassination
attempt on Ben-Gurion.

411
00:48:27.568 --> 00:48:29.900
He was recruiting
for Fatah France.

412
00:48:29.970 --> 00:48:31.267
You stopped him.

413
00:48:31.338 --> 00:48:32.862
We should have tried
to bring him to Israel.

414
00:48:32.940 --> 00:48:34.999
And Zwaiter. your harmless
little writer in Rome?

415
00:48:35.075 --> 00:48:38.306
He was behind the bomb
on El Al flight 76 in 1968.

416
00:48:38.445 --> 00:48:40.242
He was working
on another bomb
last August.

417
00:48:40.314 --> 00:48:41.406
I could go on
and on with this.

418
00:48:41.482 --> 00:48:44.042
According to evidence
nobody has seen.

419
00:48:44.118 --> 00:48:46.951
If these
people committed crimes.
we should have arrested them.

420
00:48:47.021 --> 00:48:48.511
Like Eichmann.

421
00:48:49.023 --> 00:48:50.888
If these guys live.
Israelis die.

422
00:48:50.958 --> 00:48:54.894
Whatever doubts you have.
Avner. you know this is true.

423
00:49:04.538 --> 00:49:06.802
You did well.
but you're unappy.

424
00:49:06.874 --> 00:49:09.240
I killed seven men.
Not Salameh.

425
00:49:10.077 --> 00:49:11.544
We'll get him. of course.

426
00:49:14.815 --> 00:49:16.783
You think you were
the only team?

427
00:49:17.418 --> 00:49:20.251
It's a big operation.
You were only a part.

428
00:49:20.521 --> 00:49:22.318
Does that assuage your guilt?

429
00:49:23.557 --> 00:49:25.457
Did we accomplish
anything at all?

430
00:49:25.859 --> 00:49:28.623
Every man we killed
has been replaced by worse.

431
00:49:28.696 --> 00:49:31.494
Why cut my fingernails?
They'll grow back.

432
00:49:31.765 --> 00:49:34.233
Did we kill to replace
the terrorist leadership...

433
00:49:34.301 --> 00:49:35.666
or the Palestinian leadership?

434
00:49:35.736 --> 00:49:37.431
You tell me what we've done.

435
00:49:37.504 --> 00:49:39.233
You killed them
for the sake of a country...

436
00:49:39.306 --> 00:49:40.534
you now choose to abandon.

437
00:49:42.042 --> 00:49:45.944
The country
your mother and father built.
that you were born into.

438
00:49:46.013 --> 00:49:48.709
You killed them for Munich.
for the future. for peace.

439
00:49:50.551 --> 00:49:53.679
There's no peace
at the end of this.
no matter what you believe.

440
00:49:53.754 --> 00:49:56.951
You know this is true.
Here's what I know.

441
00:49:57.157 --> 00:49:59.148
Your father is sick.
your mother will be alone.

442
00:49:59.226 --> 00:50:02.423
You're a sabra.
Your wife and daughter
are sabras.

443
00:50:03.364 --> 00:50:05.559
What I came to say
is this...

444
00:50:06.767 --> 00:50:08.098
come home.

445
00:50:22.416 --> 00:50:24.384
Come to my house
for dinner tonight.

446
00:50:26.220 --> 00:50:28.245
Come on.
You're a Jew.
you're a stranger.

447
00:50:28.322 --> 00:50:30.950
It's written someplace
or other that I'm meant to...

448
00:50:31.024 --> 00:50:33.720
ask you to come
and break bread with me.

449
00:50:34.294 --> 00:50:38.856
So break bread with me.
Ephraim.

450
00:50:42.836 --> 00:50:43.894
No.
